dcterms:description: A historical index representing the 3-month Treasury bill returns, used as a risk-free asset in the context of pension fund asset allocation.
dcterms:title: CRSP 3-month Treasury bill index

dcterms:description: A cap-weighted total return index that includes all distributions for all domestic stocks trading on major U.S. exchanges, used as a risky asset in the context of pension fund asset allocation.
dcterms:title: CRSP cap-weighted total return index

dcterms:description: A dataset containing historical market data from 1926 to 2015, used to analyze asset allocation strategies and performance.
dcterms:title: Historical market data from 1926 to 2015

dcterms:description: Synthetic data generated from a parametric model to simulate market conditions for testing asset allocation strategies.
dcterms:title: Synthetic data generated from a parametric model

dcterms:description: Bootstrap resampled data created from historical market data to test the robustness of asset allocation strategies.
dcterms:title: Bootstrap resampled data
